 -- Barak A. Pearlmutter <bap@debian.org>  Mon, 24 Nov 2014 16:58:44 +0000

stopmotion (0.8.0-1) unstable; urgency=medium

  * New upstream version
  * No longer uses libinotify
  * Fixes many issues in Ubuntu bug tracker:
    - 863965 No save dialog on exit (unnecessary as recovery is now seamless)
    - 910532 Edit operations are not correct
    - 923447 Deleting scene not undoable
    - 1194805 Resume capture will start at a random point
    - 1194818 Recovery function puts frames in the wrong order
    - 863979 Captured frames not stored on disk
    - 1069370 Cut and paste doesn't work on the timeline
    - 864052 Autosaving (recovery does this job)
    - 1036282 Onionskinning ignores changes in the timeline
    - 1050180 Framebar reentrancy causes crashes
    - 1069372 Inconsistent drag and drop behaviour
    - 1210879 We need a decent undo and recovery system
  * Other notable upstream changes and fixes:
    - Exporting gets the frames in the right order
    - Allows selection with shift+left/right
    - Correctly en/disables undo/redo/save and sets title
    - enable/disable loop button whenever play button enabled/disabled
    - onionskinning alpha value fix
    - and many more
  * Work around *.qm issue in build system: must exist in build/ prior to
    qmake to get *.qm included in install target

